Phenol (or other organic pollutants, 0.1 mM) was dissolved into 50 mL ultrapure water, followed by adding 0.05 g L−1 catalyst. After 10 min pre-adsorption, 0.3 mM PMS (or a specified amount) was added. The solution samples were periodically withdrawn using a syringe equipped with a 0.22 μm filter. All degradation tests were performed at 25 °C with constant stirring at 800 rpm. The pseudo-first-order kinetic rate constants were calculated by the following equation.2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
